posts.post_title: *** MONSTER Sale/Trade list ...complete sets...RARE cards...z11 Halla....PRICES LOWERED***
posts.post_content:
Posted By: Brian McQueen
This month's list is a little more excessive than my normal sales lists.  I'm thinking about changing my focus a bit and getting back into set collecting so many of the really scarce type cards I've accumulated can be let go in the right deal.  I've included a small list of the cards I'm looking for in trade and have also included prices next to each card just in case people want to go the "all-cash" route.  

A word of warning....many of the cards listed below represent personal favorites and cards that I spent a good deal of time trying to track down. In many cases, I had to pay an aggressive price to acquire the card.  So in turn, some of the prices below are on the aggressive side as I'm not exactly trying to push these cards out the door if you understand my meaning [IMG]https://www.net54baseball.com/images/happy.gif[/IMG]  Scans are always available upon request.  

Thanks guys,

Brian
redmaccie@hotmail.com

--------------------------

What I'm looking for

t207 Napoleon backs - need most
t210 Orange Borders - need most
w590 - Ruth, Spencer
1911 Zeenuts - Bernard, Lindsay, Melchoir, Pfyl, Ryan SF

1919 Zeenuts - Lane (oak), Nourse (oak), Pinelli (sac), Prough (sac), Vance (sac), Spencer (saltlake), Seaton (SF), Smith (SF), Snell (SF), Eastley (SEA), Arbuckle (Vern), Check (Vern), Houck (Vern), Meusel (vern)
